</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D83D3697B867EB189E50FE8FE6A4C7FA" blockId="28.[111,648,376,939]" box="[113,447,376,402]" pageId="28" pageNumber="453">ARGUMENTAIRE TAXONOMIQUE</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D83D3697B867EB189E50FE60E67AC5DE" blockId="28.[111,648,376,939]" pageId="28" pageNumber="453">
<taxonomicName id="1F824D14B867EB189E50FE60E669C7C4" authority="Druce, 1885" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1885" box="[113,370,406,433]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Hiera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gyge">
<emphasis id="EAF6EA85B867EB189E50FE60E7FBC7C5" box="[113,224,407,432]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="453">Hiera gyge</emphasis>
Druce, 1885
</taxonomicName>
est décrit du 
<collectingRegion id="1A46F875B867EB189C29FE61E57EC7C5" box="[520,613,406,432]" country="Panama" name="Chiriqui" pageId="28" pageNumber="453">Chiriqui</collectingRegion>
au 
<collectingCountry id="A0957607B867EB189E53FE41E7D0C7A5" box="[114,203,438,464]" name="Panama" pageId="28" pageNumber="453">Panama</collectingCountry>
. Il s’agit d’une petite espèce jaune et noire, peu commune, que l’on trouve dans les montagnes d’Amérique centrale. 
<bibRefCitation id="BC134B66B867EB189F7BFE02E59EC465" author="WATSON A. &amp; GOODGER D. T." box="[346,645,501,528]" pageId="28" pageNumber="453" refId="ref21163" refString="WATSON A. &amp; GOODGER D. T. 1986. - Catalogue of the NeotropicalTiger-moths. Department of Entomology, British Museum (Natural History). Occasional Papers on Systematics Entomology 1: 71 p." type="book" year="1986">Watson &amp; Goodger (1986)</bibRefCitation>
classent le genre 
<taxonomicName id="1F824D14B867EB189F3AFDE2E6C7C45A" authority="Druce, 1885" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1885" box="[283,476,532,559]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Hiera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EAF6EA85B867EB189F3AFDE2E64EC45B" box="[283,341,533,558]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="453">Hiera</emphasis>
Druce, 1885
</taxonomicName>
dans la tribu des 
<taxonomicName id="1F824D14B867EB189E4EFDC3E7DDC43B" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[111,198,564,590]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Arctiinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Arctiini">Arctiini</taxonomicName>
. Nous avons séquencé deux spécimens du 
<collectingCountry id="A0957607B867EB189E50FDA3E7FAC41B" box="[113,225,596,622]" name="Guatemala" pageId="28" pageNumber="453">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="1A46F875B867EB189ECDFDA3E675C41A" box="[236,366,596,623]" country="Guatemala" name="Baja Verapaz" pageId="28" pageNumber="453">Baja Verapaz</collectingRegion>
et 
<collectingRegion id="1A46F875B867EB189FA8FDA2E6CFC41A" box="[393,468,597,623]" country="Guatemala" name="Zacapa" pageId="28" pageNumber="453">Zacapa</collectingRegion>
) et à notre grande surprise ces séquences s’alignent systématiquement à proximité d’ 
<taxonomicName id="1F824D14B867EB189F2BFD63E520C4D8" authority="Hubner, 1827" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1827" box="[266,571,659,686]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Apistosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="judas">
<emphasis id="EAF6EA85B867EB189F2BFD63E6B8C4D8" box="[266,419,659,686]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="453">Apistosia judas</emphasis>
Hübner, 1827
</taxonomicName>
, taxon classé dans la tribu des 
<taxonomicName id="1F824D14B867EB189F50FD44E6C6C4B8" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[369,477,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Arctiinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Lithosiini">Lithosiini</taxonomicName>
. Une recherche effectuée directement avec la séquence sur l’arbre général de BOLD contenant 700 000 séquences de Lépidoptères donne une similarité uniquement avec la tribu des 
<taxonomicName id="1F824D14B867EB189F01FCC5E697C539" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[288,396,818,844]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Arctiinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Lithosiini">Lithosiini</taxonomicName>
. En conclusion le genre 
<taxonomicName id="1F824D14B867EB189E51FCA5E7B7C51E" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1885" box="[112,172,850,875]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Hiera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EAF6EA85B867EB189E51FCA5E7B7C51E" box="[112,172,850,875]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="453">Hiera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et son unique espèce 
<taxonomicName id="1F824D14B867EB189F80FCA5E6EAC51E" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1885" box="[417,497,850,875]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Hiera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gyge">
<emphasis id="EAF6EA85B867EB189F80FCA5E6EAC51E" box="[417,497,850,875]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="453">H. gyge</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sont à retirer de la tribu des 
<taxonomicName id="1F824D14B867EB189F32FC86E67DC5FE" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[275,358,881,907]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Arctiinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Arctiini">Arctiini</taxonomicName>
et doivent être placée dans la tribu des 
<taxonomicName id="1F824D14B867EB189ED1FC66E647C5DE" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[240,348,913,939]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Arctiinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Lithosiini">Lithosiini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
